    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>2018 Mathlete Fantasy Football Analysis</title>
      <link>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 29 Dec 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/</guid>
      <description>&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/htmlwidgets/htmlwidgets.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/jquery/jquery.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;link href=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/datatables-css/datatables-crosstalk.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/datatables-binding/datatables.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;link href=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/dt-core/css/jquery.dataTables.min.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;link href=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/dt-core/css/jquery.dataTables.extra.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/dt-core/js/jquery.dataTables.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;link href=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/crosstalk/css/crosstalk.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/mathlete-fantasy-football-analysis2018/index_files/crosstalk/js/crosstalk.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;section level1&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1&gt;Introduction&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In my previous &lt;a href=&#34;https://dustysturner.com/post/espn-yahoo-api-navigation/&#34;&gt;post&lt;/a&gt;, I worked through how to get your league information from the ESPN and YAHOO APIs.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The motivation for this project was to compare two leagues performances over the 2018 fantasy football season. As the ring leader of the West Point Department of Mathematical Sciences fantasy football league, we had 20 managers. This, of course, is too many for one league so we split the teams across two leagues. I managed an ESPN league, and a colleague managed a yahoo league.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Working with Dates in R</title>
      <link>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/dates-in-r/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Jun 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/dates-in-r/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id=&#34;a-little-about-dates-in-r&#34; class=&#34;section level3&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h3&gt;A Little About Dates in R&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Before we launch into any analysis that contains dates, we should know a few important nuggets about how R handles date-like objects.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There are 3 date/time classes are built in to R&lt;br /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;- Date&lt;br /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;- POSIXct&lt;br /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;- POSIXlt&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div id=&#34;base-r&#34; class=&#34;section level4&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h4&gt;Base R&lt;/h4&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First, base R can read a string of text and convert it to a date class. To help it read the date, you must tell R what date format your character string should expect. Below are several examples. You can look at all the possible format and codes by running &lt;code&gt;?strptime&lt;/code&gt; in your R console.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Tracking My Cadet&#39;s Summer Plans</title>
      <link>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/tracking-my-cadets-summer-plans/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 May 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/tracking-my-cadets-summer-plans/</guid>
      <description>&lt;!-- runtime: shiny --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;center&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Tracking my cadet’s summer plans with &lt;code&gt;dplyr&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;ggplot&lt;/code&gt;. The interactive ShinyApp is below!&#xD;&#xA;&lt;iframe src=&#34;https://dustyturner.shinyapps.io/CadetSummerInteractive/?showcase=0&#34; width=&#34;672&#34; height=&#34;1200px&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/center&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ```{r setup, include=FALSE} --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ``` --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ```{r message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, include=FALSE, paged.print=FALSE} --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- library(lubridate) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- library(tidyverse) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- library(skimr) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- library(stringr) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- library(shiny) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- travel = read_csv(&#34;CadetTravel.csv&#34;) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- # travel = read_csv(file.choose()) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ctravel = travel %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   mutate(Name = word(Name, 1)) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   mutate(Begin = as.Date(strptime(travel$Begin, format = &#34;%d-%b&#34;))) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   mutate(End = as.Date(strptime(travel$End, format = &#34;%d-%b&#34;))) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   mutate(Labeller = Begin - ((Begin-End)/2)) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   mutate(length = nchar(Name)) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   filter(Event!=&#34;Leave&#34;, Event!=&#34;Work&#34;) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   group_by(Name) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   mutate(Early = min(Begin)) %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   arrange(Early) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ``` --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ```{r, echo=FALSE} --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ui = fluidPage( --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   sliderInput(&#34;Date&#34;, label = &#34;Date:&#34;, --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--               min = as.Date(&#34;2018-05-07&#34;), max = as.Date(&#34;2018-08-15&#34;), value = today(), step = 1), --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   plotOutput(&#34;newplot&#34;) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- server = function(input,output) { --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   plot = reactive({ --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- # renderPlot(height = 1000,{ --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   trav =  ctravel %&gt;% --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   ggplot(aes(x=Begin, y = fct_reorder(farewell$Presenter, farewell$TimeStart))) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   ggplot(aes(x=Begin, y = fct_reorder(ctravel$Name,ctravel$Early, desc = TRUE))) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   geom_segment(aes(x=Begin, xend=End, yend=Name, color = Event),size=12) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   geom_text(aes(label = Event, x=Labeller), size = 2.5) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   geom_vline(xintercept=input$Date) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   theme(legend.position = &#34;none&#34;) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   xlab(&#34;Date&#34;) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   ylab(&#34;Cadet&#34;) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   ggtitle(&#34;Where Are Our Cadets?!&#34;) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   # theme_light() + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   theme(legend.position=&#34;none&#34;) + --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--     theme(axis.text=element_text(size=20), --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--         axis.title=element_text(size=14,face=&#34;bold&#34;)) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   return(trav) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   }) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   output$newplot = renderPlot(plot) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--   } --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server) --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- ``` --&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>2018 NY R Conference Presentation</title>
      <link>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/2018-ny-r-conference/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 23 Apr 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/2018-ny-r-conference/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Was honored to speak at this years &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rstats.nyc/&#34;&gt;2018 New York R Conference&lt;/a&gt; hosted by &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.landeranalytics.com/&#34;&gt;Lander Analytics&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.work-bench.com/&#34;&gt;Work-Bench&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/jaredlander&#34;&gt;Jared Lander&lt;/a&gt; sure knows how to host a good party, I mean, conference.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://dusty-turner.netlify.com/RCNYC&#34;&gt;Slides&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; are available, and you can contact me at &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:dusty.s.turner@gmail.com&#34;&gt;dusty.s.turner@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here is the youtube link to the video:&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Npk-cfQVqKo&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://img.youtube.com/vi/Npk-cfQVqKo/0.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Video&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Oh, and I got to go for a little run before the conference!&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;images/run.png&#34; width=&#34;156&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Blog Introduction</title>
      <link>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/blog-introduction/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Nov 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/blog-introduction/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;As my experience with statistics, computer science, and the all encompasing term, data science, increases, I have decided that it is time to share some of my projects.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Creating this blog serves several purposes.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ol style=&#34;list-style-type: decimal&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;It archives some projects I’ve created.&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;It makes my work public so I can receive (hopefully) constructive feedback to improve my tools/analysis.&lt;br /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;It helps me share what I’ve learned with the community that has been so helpful to me.&lt;/li&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;During the proces of learning how &lt;code&gt;blogdown&lt;/code&gt; works, I saw this timely tweet from &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/drob&#34;&gt;David Robinson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
